sentences.english: Christian dedication and faithfulness in worshiping, studying the Word, receiving the sacrament.
sentences.chinese: 在做礼拜，学习圣经，领圣餐时基督徒的奉献和忠诚。

sentences.english: Galvatron destroys him and leads the Decepticons against Earth.
sentences.chinese: 惊破天摧毁红蜘蛛，领霸天虎反扑地球。

sentences.english: SHORT skirts and cleavage have long been women s weapons.
sentences.chinese: 裙子和低V领长久以为都是女人的必杀器。

sentences.english: Set me free from my prison, that I may praise your name.
sentences.chinese: 求你领我出离被囚之地，我好称赞你的名。

sentences.english: He led them by a straight way to a city where they could settle.
sentences.chinese: 又领他们行走直路，使他们往可居住的城邑。

sentences.english: A pudgy hostess leads us to a dimly lit private room without windows.
sentences.chinese: 一个矮墩墩的女服务员领我们到了一个昏暗的包间。

sentences.english: He maketh me to lie down in green pastures; he leadeth me beside the still waters.
sentences.chinese: 他使我躺卧在青草地上，领我至可安歇的水边。

sentences.english: Go up to the land flowing with milk and honey.
sentences.chinese: 领你到那流奶与蜜之地。

sentences.english: Workers get paid by the month .

sentences.chinese: 这是要去领普立兹奖吗？

sentences.english: You can only receive money from one adult for one good deed, and cannot receive multiple rewards.
sentences.chinese: 一件事情只能从一位大人领钱，不能重复领。

sentences.english: You are right. It is my best friend and I walk it every morning.
sentences.chinese: 没错，它是我最好的朋友，我每天都领它散步。

sentences.english: The guide led us through the maze of caves.
sentences.chinese: 那个向导领我们穿过迷宫般的曲折洞穴。

sentences.english: V-neck sporty vest with a graffiti graphic print.
sentences.chinese: 领运动背心有涂鸦设计印花。

sentences.english: Matte-leather upper with an ultra-feminine collar.
sentences.chinese: 磨砂皮革鞋面超女性化的领。
